n = int(input())
    s = list(map(int, input().split()))
    s.sort()
    s.reverse()
    max_lucky = 0
    for i in range(n-1):
        if s[i] == s[i+1]:
            continue
        max_lucky = max_lucky | s[i] | s[i+1]
    print(max_lucky)

n = int(input())
    s = list(map(int, input().split()))
    s.sort()
    ans = 0
    for i in range(n-1):
        ans = max(ans, s[i]^s[i+1])
    print(ans)

n, k = map(int, input().split())
    arr = list(map(int, input().split()))
    arr.sort()
    ans = 0
    for i in range(n):
        if arr[i] > k:
            break
        else:
            ans += 1
            k -= arr[i]
    print(ans)

n, k = map(int, input().split())
    prices = list(map(int, input().split()))
    prices.sort()
    count = 0
    i = 0
    while k > 0 and i < n:
        if k - prices[i] >= 0:
            k -= prices[i]
            count += 1
        else:
            break
        i += 1
    print(count)
